Sequence Information.Peptide Name: AS-12 (synthetic AMPs, AS-16 analog, Lys-rich; XXA, UCLL1c)

Literature.Author: Zhang M, Wang J, Li C, Wu S, Liu W, Zhou C, Ma L.2024
Literature.Title: Cathelicidin AS-12W Derived from the Alligator sinensis and Its Antimicrobial Activity Against Drug-Resistant Gram-Negative Bacteria In Vitro and In Vivo.

Sequence Information.Comments: Sequence analysis: APD analysis reveals that this sequence is most similar (75%) toAS-16obtained by N-terminal sequence truncation of AS-16. K: 42%; I=F: 17%.Activity: active against E.coli ATCC 25922 or 4 clinical strains (MIC >128 ug/ml), P. aeruginosa ATCC 27853 (MIC 32 ug/ml) or 4 clinical strrains MIC >128 ug/ml,  K.pneumoniae ATCC 13883 (MIC 128 ug/ml) or higher, A.baumannii (MIC >128 ug/ml), Gram+ S. aureus ATCC 29213 (MIC 32 ug/ml), MRSA (MIC >128 ug/ml), S.epidermidis (MIC >128 ug/ml), and C.albicans (MIC 16 ug/ml) or ATCC 10231 >128 ug/ml.
